[2026-03-18T18:32:32.048Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Chain integrity verification HTTP endpoint\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: functionality\n- **Effort**: Medium (2/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (7/3)\n- **Scan Type**: feature_scout\n- **Generated**: 3/18/2026, 7:23:55 PM\n\n## Description\nExpose the existing AuditLog.verify() method via a new admin endpoint (POST /api/admin/audit/verify) that returns the ChainVerifyResult including valid status, verified count, and broken-at ID if tampered. Optionally accept a date range to verify a subset of the chain. This is a thin HTTP wrapper around already-implemented logic � the verify() method and ChainVerifyResult type are fully built.\n\n## Reasoning\nThe hash-chain verification logic is already implemented but only accessible programmatically � compliance officers and auditors have no self-service way to prove log integrity. AWS CloudTrail exposes log file validation in its console as a core compliance feature. Exposing this via HTTP closes the gap between having tamper detection and being able to demonstrate it during audits.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\n- **compact-ui-design**: Use `.claude/skills/compact-ui-design.md` for high-quality UI design references and patterns\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\n   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\n   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\")\n\n2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\n\nBegin implementation now."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"acc298eb-2a61-411d-9be8-97133940327a","uuid":"fb75869b-dbc0-4852-8990-9eeebb2c6417","timestamp":"2026-03-18T18:32:31.944Z","isSynthetic":true}
